   Droits étrangers
   THE GENTRY OF INTELLIGENCE
   Gifted children, Psychology and Schooling

   Under the name of \"intellectual precocity\", so-called \"gifted\"
   students have become an official educational issue in France. How did
   this come about? Who are these parents who consult a psychologist to
   attest their child’s great intelligence? What do they seek and what is
   their reaction? A fascinating and innovative sociological survey.

   Wilfried Lignier is a sociologist, he teaches at the École normale
   supérieure. This book follows on his PhD, obtained in 2010.
   Contact : d.ribouchon@editionsladecouverte.com
